lru-type.name: DTSR
lru-type.description: The ACA Correlator Subsystem receives the signals transmitted from antennas through optical fiber cables and processes them. For receiving the optical signals, DTS-Rs are installed on the DTP modules within the correlator. DTS-Rs receive the optical signals, convert them into electric ones, and then extract digitized data.

baci-property.description: CH3 - Bit B: Read internal parity timers. The one-second counter (24 bits) simply counts one second intervals from reset. baci-property.description: THIS SHOULD BE UINT. CH3 - Bit B: Read internal sync loss counter. The accumulation of the loss of sync occurrences will be valid 10 seconds after module power-up. It is reset when the RESET_DFR_SYNC control point is called. This value can increment by up to 3 million every 48ms (if all frames are lost). If so, the 32 bit integer containing this value will overflow (roll-over) after 69 seconds. Excessively high sync rates need to be reported to the operator.

baci-property.description: CH3 - Bit B: Read internal sync status. Reports back the number of frames the data sync engine searches before a sync is established. If a suitable signal is being received on the fiber, this should take no longer than 320 frames. However, it will continue searching, and this monitor point will continue incrementing, if a suitable signal is not present. This monitor point can also be used in conjunction with the RESET_DFR_SYNC control point for verifying the performance of the search algorithm.
